 of characters—farmers, chefs, winemakers, farm workers, and environmentalists. They include such luminaries as Warren Weber at Star Route Farm, the oldest certified organic farm in Marin County; Bob Cannard, who has supplied Chez Panisse with vegetables for decades; Sharon Grossi, the owner of the largest organic farm in Sonoma; and Craig Stoll, the founder and executive chef at Delfina in San Francisco. Raskin also offers portraits of renowned historical figures, including Luther Burbank, Jack London, and M.F.K. Fisher. Field Days is a heartfelt celebration of the farm-to-table movement and its cultural reverberations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aFarm lifezCaliforniazSonomavAnecdotes. 0aFarmerszCaliforniazSonomavBiography. 0aOrganic farmingzCaliforniazSonomavAnecdotes. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Agriculture & Food (see also POLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Agriculture & Food Policy).2bisacsh  aamerican food production.  aamerican wine.  acalifornia.  acalifornian wine.  achez panisse.  acultural studies.  adelfina.  adrinking.  aeating.  aenvironmentalism.  afarm to table movement.  afarm workers.  afarmers market.  afarming.  afarmwork.  afood and wine.  afood lovers.  ajack london.  alocal eating.  aluther burbank.  amemoir.  amfk fisher.  anorthern california.  aoak hill farm.  aorganic farming.  asonoma.  astar route farm.  aunited states of america.  avivid reportage.  awhole foods.  awine tasting.  awinemakers.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052026803640uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094318640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520943186423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520943186/original  a978-3-1